author: Second Wind
description:
This week on Unpacked, we’re taking a look at the recent layoffs that hit the Marvel Rivals development team and the complexities surrounding it; discussing the hyperfocus on video game player counts from games media and pundits alike, and then wrapping up with some interesting tidbits that have come out from interviews with now-former President of SIE Worldwide Studios, Shuhei Yoshida, and his time at PlayStation.

Intro - 00:00
Marvel Rivals Layoffs - 00:36
Player Counts - 04:17
Shuhei Yoshida Spills the Beans - 07:39
